Comment: 0,0:03:11.03,0:03:16.03,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}{旅立チ・初雪ノ頃} Setting Off - When the first snow falls
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.41,0:01:51.79,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Rio-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.52,0:01:54.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.11,0:01:55.24,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}The parts?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.96,0:01:58.04,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.63,0:02:01.04,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}If you look hard enough, you'll always find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.43,0:02:04.87,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}So warm!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.85,0:02:07.93,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I'm revived.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:13.36,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But, Rio-senpai, was it your turn for yard duty today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.70,0:02:16.64,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}There was something I wanted to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.69,0:02:33.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It's been six months since Kanata came to the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.94,0:02:36.23,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She's plays pretty well now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.23,0:02:38.30,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She just has a good teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.50,0:02:39.26,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.20,0:02:47.69,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I finally won't be needing my ear plugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.98,0:02:55.85,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Hey, madame, shouldn't you stay in town this winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.40,0:02:58.79,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.35,0:03:03.02,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I won't die that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.79,0:03:10.89,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I've been living on this mountain alone for fifty years after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.64,0:03:21.79,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Go on... Go on... Go on... Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.52,0:03:25.23,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It's finally looking like it should, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.23,0:03:27.21,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Will you be fine handling the rest on your own, Noel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.86,0:03:29.83,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Yes, I'm content.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.52,0:03:33.19,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Well, shall we have some tea then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.19,0:03:33.80,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.13,0:03:42.52,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Hey, Kureha-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.78,0:03:47.90,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Huh...? Where did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.43,0:03:50.75,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It's supposed to be here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.18,0:03:54.48,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Oh, my. What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.48,0:03:57.32,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}The military annual was here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.32,0:04:01.39,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Kanata said that she wants to know about Princess Iliya.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.58,0:04:05.26,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.26,0:04:07.17,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}If it's not there, I don't know where else it can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.57,0:04:08.97,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.87,0:04:12.29,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Naomi-san might have one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:14.59,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I'll ask her the next time I see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.59,0:04:15.30,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.85,0:04:30.90,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Princess Iliya is the eldest daughter of the current Archduke of Arcadia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.96,0:04:34.43,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I think I've told you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.43,0:04:38.04,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Anyway she's a really famous tank operator. {tempted to use tanker here. But like last eps, tanker= vehicle :)}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.04,0:04:42.12,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}A while ago, Klaus-san said "if she were alive".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.12,0:04:43.12,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:48.25,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She passed away. About two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.25,0:04:49.51,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}In the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.89,0:04:51.08,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.28,0:04:56.37,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She was assigned to the royal guard, {tl-c: not sure my timing is right on this one}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.37,0:05:01.07,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}but she dedicated herself to enhancing national influence and traveled around the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.49,0:05:07.91,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And while traveling to a city, she tried to save a child who was drowning in a river...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.23,0:05:14.12,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But, I'm quite relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.32,0:05:17.94,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}This is merely a rumor, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.37,0:05:23.48,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Iliya...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.59,0:05:25.88,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Kanata-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.35,0:05:28.54,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Yumina-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.30,0:05:30.48,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.85,0:05:43.84,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Err, it's Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.48,0:05:48.89,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Um... Yumina-san... well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.52,0:05:51.56,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}brought Yuuko-chan here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.56,0:05:56.32,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Oh, Yuuko-chan is the daughter of Martin-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.08,0:06:04.22,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Err... actually it's about an old lady named Jacott-san. She lives alone in the mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.22,0:06:07.33,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I sometimes buy vegetables and things from her in the mornings...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.44,0:06:11.58,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Oh, remember those pickled vegetables that you said were delicious the other time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.13,0:06:15.61,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It was Jacott-san who made those vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.61,0:06:21.59,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And lately no one has seen Jacott-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.45,0:06:26.67,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She's quite frail, so they're worried...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.67,0:06:30.84,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And apparently she lives quite deep in the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.84,0:06:31.83,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}and-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.83,0:06:34.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Geez... All right! All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.01,0:06:37.24,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I hear you, so just wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.23,0:06:40.24,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.77,0:06:43.82,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It's said that Princess Iliya
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.18,0:06:47.66,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}was supposed to marry the emperor of the holy city, Rome,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.66,0:06:51.34,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}to improve our relationship with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.48,0:06:54.42,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But then that would make her the third empress! {kouhi-empress, queen}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.42,0:06:56.84,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Third! The third one!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.20,0:06:58.92,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Unbelievable, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.47,0:07:01.72,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}So she'd be practically a hostage, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.66,0:07:07.10,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Well, when her highness died, that fell through,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.57,0:07:12.40,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}and we have been fighting them up until the truce earlier this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.31,0:07:16.89,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Good grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.89,0:07:18.61,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}we're finally here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.29,0:07:22.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}A partially built house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.76,0:07:26.33,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Didn't you say she lived by herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.33,0:07:27.87,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's what it was supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.71,0:07:38.75,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Madame!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.71,0:07:41.76,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.13,0:07:43.98,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Yuuko did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.98,0:07:44.78,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:47.75,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She's such a kind girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:53.16,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She's too good for that sniveler Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.16,0:07:55.23,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}This is a lovely house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.60,0:07:57.19,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:08:01.49,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I built this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.49,0:08:02.74,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.66,0:08:06.53,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Then what about the one across?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.85,0:08:10.09,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That is for my son...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.09,0:08:12.18,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}You have a son?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.67,0:08:16.17,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}He now lives in city far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.89,0:08:19.17,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}but it'd be great if he came home someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:25.67,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}So it will always be available for my son and that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.14,0:08:29.33,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I should maintain the house well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.77,0:08:45.07,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And when will your son return, Madame?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.60,0:08:47.28,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.47,0:08:50.05,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}What's coming soon, is just winter!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.05,0:08:53.55,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}You should descend the mountains the snow begins to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.55,0:08:55.33,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I cannot do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.31,0:08:58.87,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.38,0:09:02.91,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}must complete that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.91,0:09:07.46,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Before that happens, I do not plan to move even if I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:08.02,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.02,0:09:09.65,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Quit kidding already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.08,0:09:12.14,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}What about winter preparations?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.14,0:09:14.34,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Firewood? Food provisions?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.34,0:09:16.31,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}You haven't prepared anything, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.73,0:09:20.10,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It'll work out somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.10,0:09:24.50,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Thank you for your concern, young ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.15,0:09:27.17,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Madame!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.74,0:09:37.27,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Good grief, what a stubborn old lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.27,0:09:41.39,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}You're both similar, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.39,0:09:43.08,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.08,0:09:44.50,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}How am I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.50,0:09:49.00,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's because, at times, you're not true to yourself when you speak or listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.49,0:09:50.47,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.52,0:09:55.29,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Hey, that letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.29,0:09:58.08,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Why did you let me read it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.46,0:10:04.26,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I heard about it last week during communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.26,0:10:05.41,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.92,0:10:09.88,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}...the Roman army on the Eastern border has been mobilized.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:36.78,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I see. For old lady Jacott, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:37.52,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:40.01,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Take these, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.01,0:10:41.55,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.55,0:10:42.73,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.11,0:10:46.49,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}do you know how things are going with the peace talks?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.73,0:10:48.44,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.44,0:10:49.82,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.82,0:10:52.60,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}If only Princess Iliya were still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.60,0:10:54.24,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That reminds me, Martin,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.24,0:10:59.09,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}didn't Iliya-san have a younger sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.09,0:11:00.61,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Here's your 4 million back. {Pie: It's a joke from earlier.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:01.75,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's the first I've heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.18,0:11:07.68,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Well, she's not the Archduke's legitimate child, so no one talks about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:10.71,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She's third in line for the throne or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.59,0:11:14.28,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Err, is her little sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:22.99,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.99,0:11:24.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.57,0:11:26.65,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.08,0:11:32.65,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Can we walk around a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:35.65,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Hey, Kanata...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.30,0:11:39.79,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}What was the village you were born in like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.91,0:11:43.66,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Just a normal country village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:47.54,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}There were crop fields with many cows and goats,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.04,0:11:50.41,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}but there weren't many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.26,0:11:53.67,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It's probably different from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.43,0:11:56.26,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But it was a nice place, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.84,0:11:59.68,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And you have good parents, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.68,0:12:01.27,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I can tell by looking at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.82,0:12:05.52,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}What kind of place did you grow up in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.57,0:12:12.03,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I grew up in a small village near the capital,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.54,0:12:16.99,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}surrounded by beautiful forests and lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.31,0:12:22.21,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I lived there with my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.81,0:12:24.07,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It was boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.72,0:12:27.25,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}A peaceful life where nothing ever happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.84,0:12:34.94,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}My one comfort was my beloved sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.97,0:12:40.57,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}We had different mothers, but she came to visit once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:43.46,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I admired her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.03,0:12:46.79,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She was beautiful and kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.79,0:12:49.78,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And she accepted her fate silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.37,0:12:54.07,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I learned the trumpet from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.07,0:12:57.38,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But she was too kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.25,0:13:01.41,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}and because of her kindness, she gave her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.60,0:13:07.46,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}When I first came here, I thought this town was like a labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.05,0:13:15.59,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I got lost and ended up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.59,0:13:18.71,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I felt like I had finally reached my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.03,0:13:23.72,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But I realized later
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.71,0:13:27.06,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}that this was merely a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.39,0:13:31.78,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.57,0:13:36.84,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I often get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.84,0:13:37.82,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.31,0:13:40.00,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I like being lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.20,0:13:46.34,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It's all right to be lost, isn't it? Even if it's a dead end!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.15,0:13:52.93,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's how I met you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.50,0:14:03.31,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}At times, I envy you, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.28,0:14:12.57,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}If only I could be that true to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.03,0:14:33.01,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:36.76,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Why are you so concerned about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:42.06,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}You're similar, to my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.93,0:14:47.10,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I don't remember having a pretty daughter like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.01,0:14:51.69,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She had a forbidden love, and gave birth to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.69,0:14:53.67,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She always waited for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.67,0:14:57.51,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}A man who may or may not come by once a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.96,0:15:03.12,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Mother lived an unfortunate life like that, until she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.96,0:15:08.62,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Why did you think that she was unfortunate?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:09.89,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's because-
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.89,0:15:11.87,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I am happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.98,0:15:18.73,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}He promised he would come back. {tl-c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.73,0:15:21.46,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That he would come get me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.46,0:15:24.06,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That promise alone, was enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.06,0:15:24.89,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}How could that be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.09,0:15:30.03,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}What else could I have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.03,0:15:31.48,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.48,0:15:35.35,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}If there were other things I could do, I might have done them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.84,0:15:37.16,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.91,0:15:40.14,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Is that enough for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.14,0:15:42.03,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Are you content with just that? Is that really happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.94,0:15:46.21,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Because I have memories of loving him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.80,0:15:52.26,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I have my memories of him and the hope that I will see him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.10,0:15:54.54,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:15:57.01,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That is more than enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.59,0:16:11.15,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I thought it was getting cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.04,0:16:35.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}It was on a snowy night like this that I first met you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.33,0:16:46.43,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}When Madame was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.57,0:16:48.31,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Seize was a thriving resort city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.70,0:17:11.40,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She fell in love with the young heir of a rich merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.69,0:17:21.29,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And soon, she had his child,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.26,0:17:25.34,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}but that man already had a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.88,0:17:31.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}A blessing or not, that man's wife couldn't have a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:36.37,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}so he took her child and went back home,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.36,0:17:43.86,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}with the promise that he would one day come back for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.00,0:18:14.40,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}{\an8}Madame! Madame!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:14.40,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Now that I'm old, I sometimes think...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.81,0:18:17.56,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Back then, if only...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.31,0:18:22.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}{\an8}Old lady Jacott!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.31,0:18:22.11,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Life...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.32,0:18:25.46,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}is a cycle of loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.39,0:18:29.32,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But before you can lose, you must first gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.32,0:18:31.41,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}However, the happier you are from your gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.01,0:18:36.18,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}the greater your pain is when it's lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.93,0:18:45.77,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But if you have the memories of your happiness...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.84,0:18:50.75,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}With those memories, a person can live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.89,0:18:58.31,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.31,0:19:01.70,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}This may not be a great time, but I found it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.70,0:19:03.41,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}the picture of Princess Iliya.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.41,0:19:04.10,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Naomi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.81,0:19:06.99,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Filicia, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.66,0:19:09.83,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I think it must have been five years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.83,0:19:12.84,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}when the Princess came to Seize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.95,0:19:18.47,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Is that Shuko?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.03,0:19:31.33,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Rio-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.42,0:20:29.91,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Actually, I think my parents must have wished
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.56,0:20:34.35,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}for me to find a husband and succeed the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.95,0:20:40.54,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But, I was enchanted by the sound of that trumpet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.93,0:20:43.97,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}and I simply couldn't forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.08,0:20:46.32,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.47,0:20:49.35,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Iliya-san, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.01,0:20:54.47,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}So, you really did meet her too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.38,0:20:57.19,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}How wonderful it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.68,0:21:00.47,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}the sound of Iliya-san that resounds in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.01,0:21:04.40,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Then you and I met.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:11.86,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I think I may have been running away, to this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.26,0:21:15.14,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}So at first, nothing really mattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.59,0:21:19.61,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I thought it was just a place, that I'd leave eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.67,0:21:22.94,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}But now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.60,0:21:26.30,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I truly do not want to leave this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.79,0:21:30.75,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}That's probably why I must go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.99,0:21:33.38,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.67,0:21:37.34,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}There is something that only I can do after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.19,0:21:45.54,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}I do not intend to say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.61,0:21:51.88,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}No matter how far we are separated...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.73,0:21:56.03,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}The sound will echo...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.37,0:21:58.40,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}The sound echoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.85,0:22:02.67,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}...and reach out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.48,0:22:09.71,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Kanata, have I been a good senpai to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.51,0:22:13.46,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.52,0:22:33.52,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}And so, Rio-senpai left us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.96,0:22:39.13,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}She left a sound that will continue to echo in my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.77,0:22:40.83,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}...a wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.52,0:22:44.24,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}...wonderful sound of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.97,0:24:18.97,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}Next time:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.97,0:24:19.89,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}A Visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.89,0:24:21.05,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}A Blazing Field of Snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.05,0:24:23.05,Sora no Woto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.12,0:00:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3}
